Mr Massengill, who was in his uniform, was 'frantically pounding on the door' of the firehouse when paramedics came to the rescue, the Dunwoody Police Department said in a Facebook post.

He and the paramedics reached the car just in time to help Jennifer deliver the baby, according to  WSB-TV.

Though Mrs Massengill wanted to get out of the car, there was no time and the baby was delivered in the car sitting in the firestation's parking lot.

